    "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eTkcQVc0-YU"
  }, "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eTkcQVc0-YU")), mdx("p", null, "Tomorrow, another kind of flavor entirely, another primary color in the crayon box, if you will."), mdx("h2", {
    "id": "a-reciprocal-note-the-fourth"
  }, "A Reciprocal Note: The Fourth"), mdx("p", null, "All the notes I\u2019ve discussed so far are found above and to the right of the tonic, in the northeast quadrant of the map. These notes are generated by multiplication alone."), mdx("p", null, "What about the notes that are generated by division? These are found to the left and down on the lattice."), mdx("p", null, "The closer a note is to the tonic, the smaller the numbers are, and the easier it is for the ear to tell where it is. I\u2019ll cover this much more in later posts, but I think the character of an individual note, its unique harmonic color, is largely determined by two signals it sends to the ear and mind:"), mdx("ol", null, mdx("li", {
