  }, "The Major Scale"), mdx("p", null, "The notes 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 and 7, clustered at the center of the lattice, constitute a major scale. This tuning uses the smallest ratios (the ones with the lowest numbers) available for each position in the scale. It goes back at least to Ptolemy in the 100\u2019s AD."), mdx("p", null, mdx("a", {
