    "href": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qWyp-5VpDAc&feature=emb_title"
  }, "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qWyp-5VpDAc&feature=emb_title")), mdx("p", null, "The new note is a mirror of the 3, an upside-down 3. Its ratio is 1/5, which can be octave-shifted to 8/5. That ratio puts it a little over halfway up the scale, between the 5 and the 6. It\u2019s called the minor sixth or flatted sixth; I use the symbol b6."), mdx("p", null, "There is a beautiful shift of feeling when you move from overtonal energy to reciprocal and back again. To me it feels like breathing in and out. Maybe that\u2019s because I play harmonica. When you blow on a few holes of a Marine Band, you get the 1 chord. When you draw, you get the 4. Breathing in and out takes you back and forth between reciprocal and overtonal territory."), mdx("p", null, mdx("a", {
