    parentName: "p"
  }, "When I first found my own voice inside a minor triad, I couldn\u2019t believe it was so \u2014 well, so (arggh! I can scarcely say the dreaded word, but here goes) \u2014 so \u2026 happy. There. We are told from the beginning that minor is sad, the designated mode for angst and funerals. Well, to be honest, the equal-tempered version of the minor third is rather sad. ", "[It]", " is too narrow, or flat. So piano minor is flat and sounds dull \u2014 the fire is out of it. But minor thirds in just intonation, and the minor triads they support, are swift and burning. They have the gypsy left in them, and do some leaping kind of dance.")), mdx("p", null, "\u2013 W.A. Mathieu, Harmonic Experience, p. 55"), mdx("p", null, "The gypsy really comes out to dance when it\u2019s actual music, but to get an idea, here\u2019s that same seesaw between minor and major. This time it\u2019s tuned to equal temperament."), mdx("p", null, mdx("a", {
