  }, "The Minor Second"), mdx("p", null, "The last three notes (b6, b3 and b7) are related to each other. They all contain a reciprocal third. There is a family resemblance of sound and function. (They also all happen to be a little flat in equal temperament. On a guitar it\u2019s a nice trick to bend them a little to sweeten them.)"), mdx("p", null, "Here is another note in the family, farther out harmonically, the minor second:"), mdx("p", null, mdx("a", {
