  }, "More Experimenting"), mdx("p", null, "Yesterday, I described a simple way to hear, and more importantly, feel, the difference between equal temperament and just intonation, by singing Fr\xE8re Jacques over an open G chord with ET major thirds, and then over a G chord that has only roots and fifths in it."), mdx("p", null, "The second half of the experiment is called ", mdx("a", {
    parentName: "p",
    "href": "http://www.matthewdallman.com/essay_object/to_sing_world_object.html"
  }, "singing over a drone"), ", and it\u2019s a great way to get acquainted with the resonance of the pure notes. The 1\u20135 drone is a bedrock foundation of ", mdx("a", {
